OL,5, An ex-funeral home owner and her mother
OL,6, have been sentenced in Colorado after  
OL,7, selling body parts without any consent.
OL,9,FMegan Hess, 46, and Shirly Koch, 69,   
OL,10,Fdissected some 560 corpses between 2010
OL,11,Fand 2018, selling parts to medical     
OL,12,Ftraining companies which did not know  
OL,13,Fthey had been fraudulently acquired.   
OL,15,FEntire bodies were sold in some cases, 
OL,16,Fprosecutors said. It is legal in the US
OL,17,Fto donate organs, but not sell them.   
OL,19,FHess was sentenced to 20 years in jail 
OL,20,Fand Koch to 15.                        
